cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless networks and their capacity. 
2. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also likely as the paper analyzes the notion of capacity under game-theoretic constraints. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as the paper deals with the transfer of information in wireless networks. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper introduces a new optimization problem called the Maximum Perfect Dominated Set (MaxPDS) problem. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper deals with the capacity of wireless networks under game-theoretic constraints.
